---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import ManufacturerNote from '../../components/ManufacturerNote.astro';
import EditorialImage from '../../components/EditorialImage.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';

const title = 'Clip-In Hair Extensions Manufacturing';
const description =
  'Clip-In hair extensions manufactured by Sach & Vogue Hair — removable professional sets, 1/3/5/7 piece options, U-Clip and U-Part logic, sewing quality, and colour planning.';
const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Hair Extensions', href: '/hair-extensions/' },
  { label: 'Clip-In Hair Extensions' },
];
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description} path="/clip-in-hair-extensions/" {breadcrumbs}>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
      <h1>Clip-In hair extensions manufacturing</h1>
      <p class="section__lead">
        Removable professional sets built from sorted bulk human hair — with reinforced sewing, balanced clip distribution, and piece architecture planned for salon cutting and client comfort.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--compact">
    <div class="container article-body">
      <EditorialImage
        src="/images/clip-in-hair-extensions.webp"
        alt="Clip-in hair extension wefts with metal clips in multiple professional salon shades"
        width={1448}
        height={1086}
        class="editorial-image--inline"
      />
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Clip-In Hair Extensions offer a removable option for clients who want flexibility without a semi-permanent install. Sach &amp; Vogue Hair manufactures clip-in sets for professional salons — not mass-market consumer packs with uneven weft quality. Each set is built to be cut, layered, and integrated with the client&apos;s haircut.</p>

        <h2>Professional set architecture</h2>
        <ul class="topic-list">
          <li><strong>1-piece sets</strong> — volume panels for targeted boost or retail simplicity.</li>
          <li><strong>3-piece sets</strong> — classic layout for partial volume and length.</li>
          <li><strong>5-piece sets</strong> — fuller coverage for layered cutting and styling flexibility.</li>
          <li><strong>7-piece sets</strong> — comprehensive sets for significant transformation and editorial styling.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>U-Clip and U-Part logic</h2>
        <p>U-Clip configurations support parting-friendly placement; U-Part sets integrate with the client&apos;s natural part for believable crown and mid-section volume. Piece placement maps should be planned before manufacturing so clip density matches the target haircut — not added as an afterthought.</p>

        <h2>Manufacturer quality: sewing, clips, distribution</h2>
        <p>Clip-in longevity depends on double-weft sewing where needed, snap clip strength, and even weight distribution across pieces. Poor sewing sheds under brushing; poor clip placement creates tension points. We manufacture with salon daily-use in mind.</p>

        <ManufacturerNote title="Colour, density, and length planning">
          <p>Clip-ins must be specified with the same consultation discipline as semi-permanent methods — shade code, target length, density per piece, and how the set will be cut to the client&apos;s layers. A correct gram total in the wrong piece map still fails the blend.</p>
        </ManufacturerNote>

        <h2>Salon and retail applications</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom sets cut and layered to match a client&apos;s haircut</li>
          <li>Salon retail for clients who prefer removable volume</li>
          <li>Trial formats before committing to tape, keratin, or weft installs</li>
          <li>Event and editorial styling with professional-grade hair</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Related: <a href="/hair-extension-colours-colour-code-guide/">Colour Code Guide</a> · <a href="/wholesale-hair-extensions/">Wholesale supply</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <CTASection heading="Clip-In set enquiry" text="Share piece count, target length, shade code, and whether the set is for cutting integration or retail." />
</BaseLayout>
